name: Security Tamper Proof Screwdriver Bit Set 100 pcs
description:
100 Piece Security Bit Set

A complete set of security bits to give you full access to protected components. A must for DIY-ers!

Set Includes

  • Phillips: #0, #1,#3, (5)#2
  • Pozi: #0, #1,#3, (5)#2
  • Slotted: 3, 4, 4.5, 5, 5.5, 6, 6.5, 7, 8mm
  • Square: #0, 1, 2, 3
  • Spanner: #4, 6, 8, 10
  • Torx: T-8, 10, 15, 20, 25, 27, 30, 40, 45
  • Hollow-Tip Torx: T-8, 10, 15, 20, 25, 27, 30, 35, 40
  • Torq-Set: #6, 8, 10
  • Metric Hex: 1.5, 2, 2.5, 3, 4, 5, 5.5, 6, 8mm
  • Hollow Metric Hex: 2, 2.5, 3, 4, 5, 6
  • SAE Hex: 1/16, 5/64, 3/32, 7/64, 1/8, 9/64, 5/32, 3/16, 7/32, 1/4
  • Hollow SAE Hex: 5/64, 3/32, 7/64, 1/8, 9/64, 5/32
  • Spline: M5, M6, M8
  • Clutch: #1, 2, 3
  • Tri-Wing: #1, 2, 3, 4
  • Hex end to 1/4 drive adapter
  • Magnetic hex bit driver
  • One y-design hook hanging bit
  • 1/4 hex to 1/4 socket wobble adapter
  • 1/4 hex wobble adapter
  • Durable hard plastic case

Ship Weight: 1.5 lbs
short_description: 100 bits to remove every screw imaginable. Contains Torx, torque, spanner, phillips, hollow tip SAE and Metric hex bits, and more!
product_name: Security Tamper Proof Screwdriver Bit Set 100 pcs

name: Aven MightyScope USB Digital Microscope 200X with Stand
description:
A compact digital microscope with a USB interface and 10x-200x magnification!

Click Here to go to our MightyScope image gallery

The Digital Age
 Digital image capture, storage and manipulation is ushering in a new age in microscopy. Digital microscope cameras provide you a broader range of functionality, flexibility and portability, expanding your capabilities beyond the traditional optical laboratory microscope.

 

The Mighty Scope is lightweight, handy, and amazingly easy to use! Plug it into the USB port of your PC or laptop and you're ready to go! All it takes is a simple press of the Microtouch shutter trigger to quickly and convenient capture your magnified image. With its high resolution magnification (10X - 200x), simple operation, and compact size, The Mighty Scope puts the world of microphotography at your fingertips.

CML#-313-050

 

 

Features:

Easy to use, 6-LED hand-held digital microscope with a USB interface.

Can be used for science and engineering work, dermatology, detailed repair, assembly and quality control
(i.e. electronics, mechanical, etc), hobbies & collecting (coin, stamp, watch, jewelry, etc.), law enforcement
(counterfeit ID, crime lab, etc), entertainment and much more.

High resolution magnification at your fingertips. Detailed examination of any area you choose.

LED intensity can be adjusted using control wheel on body, and
an adjustable magnification from10X - 200X, all in one compact lens.

Microtouch Shutter trigger allows for convenient image capture when in hand held mode or mounted
on a stand.

Mighty Scope comes with software for easy capture of images or videos (measurement function included) and
adjustable stand. Optional boom type stand is also available.

Just plug into a PC and you are set to go!

 

Specs:
Aven Model: 26700-200
Image Sensor: 1/4" Color CMOS
Effective Pixels (HxV): 1280 x 1024
Signal Output: USB 2.0
Magnification: 10x to 200x
LED Light Type: 6 White LEDs
Working Distance: 10x: 150mm | 20x: 95mm | 50x: 13mm

Anytime an abrasive substance is handled and microscopic particles are a detriment, titanium is a good choice. Titanium is non-magnetic therefore is extremely useful when handling magnetic materials, or when working in a magnetic field.

Pattern OO tweezer has flat edges, heavy duty strong blades that taper to regular strong points. Overall length 4-3/4".

name: Chemtronics Circuitworks No-Clean Electronic Grade Rework Flux
meta_description: TAcky Paste Flux for rework of SMT and SMD devices.
description:
Designed for BGA and QFP repair. Perfect for use when reflowing the GPU during Xbox-360 "Ring Of Death" Repairs

3.5 Gram (0.12oz) syringe

CW8500 is a high-viscosity No-Clean paste flux developed to assist in printed circuit board rework or repair. It is an effective paste flux for prototype work where a small amount of flux is needed on a specific area of a board or assembly. After being dispensed, rework flux stays in place until soldering occurs. Exhibits excellent performance in applications requiring a flux having good thermal stability such as surface mount component or repair.

It is the ideal choice for QFP or BGA rework operations. It is also well suited for use with through-hole repair operations.

Features:
  • High Viscosity- stays where you put it.
  • Residues are non-corrosive, so not need to be removed after soldering
  • Compatible with most no-clean solders and fluxes.
  • Excellent consistency with stable viscosity
  • Lead Free - RoHS compliant.
  • May be used with leaded or lead-free solders.
  • Stored in a controlled environment. 2 year shelf life.
A few warnings and cautions:
  • For industrial use only
  • We can not offer advice on a specific application. For use by experienced electronics technicians
  • User assumes all risk for application.
  • Any warrantees are limited to replacement or refund of product.
  • Always wear safety glasses when working with soldering equipment and materials
  • Always use adequate ventilation when working with soldering equipment and materials
  • Avoid breathing flux fumes emitted during soldering.
  • Flux fumes may cause pulmonary irritation or damage.
  • This product may contain chemicals known to the state of California to cause cancer and/or other reproductive harm.

Ship weight: 4 ounces
short_description: 3 CC syringe for convenient dispensing during electronic repairs.

name: Kester 44 Rosin Core Solder 63/37 .031" 1 lb. Spool
meta_description: Kester "44" solder wire for electronics applications
description:
Kester "44" has virtually dominated the field of activated rosin core solders for well over four decades. An outstanding performance feature of this flux is the "instant-action" wetting behavior. The high mobility and fast-spreading action of this flux results in more reliable production line soldering.

Features:
  • Kester "44" Item Number 24-6337-0027
  • 67/37 Tin/Lead, .031" Diameter is most common for electronics work
  • High activity RA formulation
  • Excellent solderability to a wide variety of metallizations
  • Industry standard for decades
  • Standard Core 66 (3.3% flux)
  • Solder iron tip temperatures between 315-371°C (600-700°F)
  • Flux residue is non-corrosive and non-conductive
  • Shelf life 2 years from DOM

A few warnings and cautions: * For industrial use only * We can not offer advice on a specific application. name: Kester 245 No Clean Wire Solder 63/37 .031" 1 lb. Spool
meta_description: Kester "245" solder wire for electronics applications
description:
Kester 245 No-clean Cored Wire was developed to complement low residue liquid fluxes being used by the electronics industry. The chemistry is based on some of the same principles that have been safely used for years in mildly activated rosin fluxes. The use of 245 No-clean Cored Wire results in visually acceptable assemblies without cleaning, yet soldering quality and efficiency is comparable to that obtained with mildly activated rosin flux.
Features:
  • Highly reliable post-soldering residue
  • Minimal residue
  • 67/37 Tin/Lead alloy

Legendary Kester Solder in a convenient Dispense-Pak Saves You Money!

This is a 35 gram syringe - includes bonus dispensing tips

Kester EP 256 is a paste solder developed for high volume SMT reflow soldering. It is a no-clean, air or nitrogen reflowable, solder paste specifically designed for maximum robustness in reflow profiling. EP256 has the widest possible reflow processing window.

Residues that remain after soldering are almost colorless, leaving a cosmetically appealing repair. The residue has high electrical resistance and is safe to be left on the assembly after soldering.

name: Soldering Iron Tip Cleaning Wire Sponge
meta_description: soldering iron cleaning sponge
description:
Cleans your soldering iron tips without water! Made from coils of brass, which is softer than the tip plating yet harder than the oxidation that forms on the tip. To clean the tip, simply plunge (stab) the iron tip into the coils. The ideal alternative to a wet sponge.

Compare to $12.99 for the "Brand Name" ball of brass!

  • "shell" design keeps the solder from splattering
  • Will not reduce the tip temperature
  • A great alternative to the conventional damp sponge
  • May be used as a portable tool holder and cleaner
  • Compatible with Hakko Tip cleaners and brass replacement ball
short_description: Cleans your soldering iron tips without water!

name: Kester 331 Water Soluble Flux Solder 63/37 .031" 1 lb. Spool
meta_description: Kester "331" solder wire for electronics applications
description:
Kester 331 Rosin Core Solder 63/37 .031" 1 lb. Spool

Kester 331 is a water soluable formula flux-cored solder wire. More heat stable than most organic fluxes, using this solder wire results in minimal smoke and odor, and can be removed with a water rinse.

Kester 331 organic flux is more effective than rosin fluxes when soldering difficult metals such as copper, nickel and brass. High heat stability allows for minimal smoke and odor. NOTE: Extremely active. Residues may need to be removed ater soldering.

Kester 24-6337-6403 Features:
  • Wire diameter: .031 is most common for electronics work"
  • Alloy: Sn63Pb37 (63% Tin / 37% Lead)
  • Melting range: 361°F (183°C)
  • Core flux type: Water Soluable
  • Core size: 66
  • Spool size: 1 lb.
  • Factory fresh, not used or surplus material
  • Shelf life: 3 years from DOM
  • RoHS compliant: No
A few warnings and cautions:

  • We can not offer advice on a specific application. For use by experienced electronics technicians
  • User assumes all risk for application.

  • Always use adequate venilation when working with soldering equipment and materials
  • Avoid breathing flux fumes emitted during soldering.

  • This product may contain chemicals known to the state of California to cause cancer and/or other reproductive harm.

  • Will not reduce the tip temperature
  • A great alternative to the conventional damp sponge

name: Gold Kapton Tape Polyimide High Temp 1" x 36yds 25mm
meta_description: High temperature tape commonly used in electronics repair.
description:
PREMIUM QUALITY, not to be compared with cheaper imported tapes.

High temperature tape is widely used for masking during powder coating, wave soldering, circuit board production, or holding parts in place during hot air rework or repair of electronic components.Due to it's semi-transparent shiny gold color is also has a myriad of hobby and craft uses.

Commonly used in electronics repair, it is the ideal choice for QFP or BGA rework operations. It is also well suited for use with through-hole repair operations.

  • High temperature tape will not burn or wrinkle
  • 1 mil polyimide film & 1.5 mil silicone adhesive
  • Clean removal, no residue
  • Residues are non-corrosive
  • Note: although varying widths are pictured, this includes ONE ROLL of the size specified above

meta_description: High temperature tape commonly used in electronics repair.

PREMIUM QUALITY, not to be compared with cheaper imported tapes.

High temperature tape is widely used for masking during powder coating, wave soldering, circuit board production, or holding parts in place during hot air rework or repair of electronic components.Due to it's semi-transparent shiny gold color is also has a myriad of hobby and craft uses.

Commonly used in electronics repair, it is the ideal choice for QFP or BGA rework operations. It is also well suited for use with through-hole repair operations.

  • Clean removal, no residue

name: Daylight Ultra-Slim 7" ESD Safe Magnifier Lamp Black U22091
meta_description: Daylight Ultra-Slim ESD Safe Magnifier for inspection, manufacturing, hobbies, crafts, needlework.
description:
See all the details you've been missing with this extra-large lens! This unique, stylish slimline magnifying light is ideal for your most precision work.

Daylight technology renders colors and details more accurately. Perfect for hobbies or crafts, inspection or manufacturing.

 The Daylight Ultra Slim ESD Magnifying Lamp provides full protection against static electricity and electrostatic discharge (ESD). The COMPLETE lamp (Head, Lens, Joint & Arm) is grounded and has special static dissipative materials to smoothly take away static charges in a controlled manner, preventing any build up of static electricity which gives complete protection against ESD events.

With bright 28w Daylight™ light and the unique 17.5cm/7” precision optical white glass lens, this lamp combines the latest innovations in lighting design. The Daylight™ energy saving tube ensures that you have plenty of comfortable daylight light to work with.

Includes bonus 1.5" diameter 4X add-on swing arm lens!

Features:
  • Slim head design for optimal viewing without restrictions
  • 7" 3-diopter (1.75X) glass lens
  • 1.5" 12-diopter (4X) glass swing-arm lens
  • Lens is clear, optically perfect glass
  • Uses a unique 28-watt (150W equivalent) low heat Daylight tube
  • Heavy-duty metal arm with internal safety springs.
  • Includes table clamp and bulb
  • Electronic ballast for flicker-free light
  • Heavy-duty metal arm construction

60 day no-hassle return policy on this item. 2 Year factory warranty. Ship Weight: 12 pounds

Daylight™ technology With full spectrum Daylight™ technology, your eyes will still be fresh at the end of the day! No headaches, no red-eyes, working under Daylight™ becomes as relaxing and natural as a walk in the park. Energy saving All Daylight™ bulbs and tubes use 80% less energy. When you work with your lamp, you reduce your electricity bill and do your bit for the planet.
ESD safe Independently verified to be suitable for use in EPA (Electrostatic Protected Areas - IEC 61340-5-1 and ANSI/ESD 20:20) ideal for use on workstations where ESD sensitive devices are being handled Flicker-free Experience the Flicker-Free light revolution with Daylight. No stroboscope effect, no headaches, just a pure soothing light to relax your eyes!
Independenlty tested TÜV Product Service have independently performed and passed a 10,000 cycle endurance / quality test to all moving parts. TÜV SÜD AG Munich, Germany is an independent Testing, Certification and Inspection body. UL & CE Certification All Daylight™ lamps are officially UL & CE certified to ensure they adhere to the latest American and European standards for lighting and electrical appliances.

description:
Techspray Plato TT-95 Tip Tinner Lead-Free, ESD Safe, No Residue

0.7 ounce canister

Plato's TT-95 LEAD FREE Tip Tinner is a fast, efficient, and safe means of re-tinning tips. This thermally-stable compound is residue free and environmentally and ESD-safe.

A well tinned soldering tip improves operator performance and satisfaction. Plato's TT95 Tip-Tin provides improved cleaning and re-tinning of highly oxidized soldering iron tips safely and efficiently. Just wipe the oxidized soldering tip at normal soldering temperature into the tip tinner for a few seconds until the bright tinning surrounds the working end of the tip, then wipe the excess residue on a wet cellulose sponge - it's that easy!

Features:

The chemistry is based on some of the same principles that have been safely used for years in mildly activated rosin fluxes. The use of 245 No-clean Cored Wire results in visually acceptable assemblies without cleaning, yet soldering quality and efficiency is comparable to that obtained with mildly activated rosin flux.

name: Chemtronics Circuitworks CW8100 Soldering Flux Pen Low-Solids, No-Clean
meta_description: Tacky Paste Flux for rework of SMT and SMD devices.
description:
The CW8100 Flux Pen is a unique tool for rework and touch-up soldering. It allows controlled application of flux, eliminating the mess from flux bottles. The chisel point allows for work in very confined spaces. The flux pen is ideally suited for tab assembly no-clean and surface mount rework application because it can deliver flux to a specific area.

CW8100 is a halogen-free, non-rosin organic Flux Pen that is specifically designed for rework of conventional and surface mount circuit board assemblies. The extremely low solids content and nature of the activator system results in practically NO RESIDUE left on the assembly after soldering. There are no residues to interfere with electrical testing. CW8100 exhibits improved soldering performance to minimize solder bridges (shorts) during rework operations.

Residues that remain after soldering are almost colorless, leaving a cosmetically appealing repair. The residue has high electrical resistance is safe to be left on the assembly after soldering.

Features:
  • 9gram (0.32oz) Chisel-tip marker Applicator
  • For rework and touch-up of SMT, SMD, and through hole solder joints
  • Suitable for automotive, computer, telecom
  • Low Solids Content for practically NO Residue
  • Compatible with Lead and Lead-Free Solders
  • Lead Free - RoHS compliant.
  • Stored in a controlled environment
  • Guaranteed 2 years expiration date from date of ship!
A few warnings and cautions:
  • For industrial use only
  • We can not offer advice on a specific application. For use by experienced electronics technicians
  • User assumes all risk for application.
  • Any warrantees are limited to replacement or refund of product.
  • Always wear safety glasses when working with soldering equipment and materials
  • Always use adequate venilation when working with soldering equipment and materials
  • Avoid breathing flux fumes emitted during soldering.
  • Flux fumes may cause pulmonary irritation or damage.
  • This product may contain chemicals known to the state of California to cause cancer and/or other reproductive harm.
